=== G-12-renting-apartment: Renting an Apartment (B1) ===
Opening: Hello, this is the apartment manager speaking. How can I help you?

[normal inquiry]
  IN:  Hi, I'm calling about the apartment for rent on Main Street.
  OUT: Yes, it's still available. Would you like to come see it?

[short answer]
  IN:  $800.
  OUT: I see you're asking about the rent. The apartment on Main Street is $800 per month. Would you like to come see it?

[chinese intent]
  IN:  我想看看房子。
  OUT: 可以这样说："I'd like to see the apartment." 这句话适合在电话里告诉房东你想看房。Which apartment are you calling about?

[detail question]
  IN:  How many bedrooms does it have?
  OUT: It has two bedrooms and one bathroom. Would you like to come see it?

=== G-12-renting-apartment: Renting an Apartment (retest) ===
[normal]
  IN:  How many bedrooms does it have?
  OUT: It has two bedrooms and one bathroom. Would you like to come see it?
